.SH "NAME"
rio_dev_get \- Increments the reference count of the RIO device structure
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'struct\ rio_dev\ *\ rio_dev_get('u
.BI "struct rio_dev * rio_dev_get(struct\ rio_dev\ *\ " "rdev" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIrdev\fR
.RS 4
RIO device being referenced
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Each live reference to a device should be refcounted\&.
.PP
Drivers for RIO devices should normally record such references in their
\fBprobe\fR
methods, when they bind to a device, and release them by calling
\fBrio_dev_put\fR, in their
\fBdisconnect\fR
methods\&.
